Interface ICommandExecutor

    • Method Detail

      • execute

        <T> CommandResult<T> execute(ICommand<?> command,
                             CommandContext context,
                             java.lang.Object opt)

        Executes the command with the provided command class CommandContext and any optional data.

        Parameters:
        command - The command to execute.
        context - The context of the command, containing the calling alias and any args it may have.
        opt - A nullable vararg of Any, which can be useful in specific implementations when a command requires more than just context for execution.
        Returns:
        class CommandResult The result after command execution.
        See Also:
        class CommandContext
